<div class="en">
Together with your children
find sound-making objects in the home
Use existing instruments
Raid the kitchen cupboard
or make your own.

Discover
loud and soft sounds
long and short sounds
high and low pitches
bright and dark colours
Spend time to explore them
and make them close their eyes
to listen to the resonance.

Make your own musical score together
(there are no fixed rules)
Use many colours to represent
the different elements
Let your child lead the process
Then perform it together.
